users.name: Administrator
users.about: Founder, Owner, and Operator of Cafe Connect, as well as several fortune 500 companies.

users.name: Test User
users.about: I love black coffee to start my day and looking for the coziest warmest atmospheres to enjoy my cup of joe each day. Please enjoy my reviews of local spots and I look forward to seeing your experiences as well!

users.name: Suzanne Warner
users.about: Just a small town girl living in a lonely world. Born and raised in South Detroit. On a midnight train headed to coffee town.

users.name: William Worthright
users.about: I am a very successful business owner who only accepts my iced mochas from the most classy establishments. My only requirement is that they must have a drive thru lane.

users.name: Jack O'Daniel
users.about: Big fan of strong espresso-based drinks. I love a hipster vibes and obscure menus.

users.name: Samuel Dursley
users.about: I am open to any coffee shop experiences, I have never really explored coffee shops besides places like Starbucks, but I'm looking forward to expanding my taste! Added bonus if the menus include some international brews or drinks I have never heard of, I would definitely try them!

users.name: Michaela Scott
users.about: Regional manager at Flunder Difflin Paper Company, so I spend a lot of time hanging around the coffee pot in the break room. Looking for places where I can find simliar friendly interactions as my local workplace coffee pot.

users.name: Mike Scott
users.about: I recently was released from prison, and the thing I missed most was good quality coffee. Can't wait to start exploring local coffee shops. I would love to find some places which have outdoor seating since I have been locked up so long. EDITED!

users.name: Vickie Mettenberger
users.about: My name is Vickie, I love to start every day with a delicious mocha frappaccino with extra shots of caramel and vanilla. I'm looking for some modern downtown aestethics where I can plug in my laptop and get some work done for my new social media influencing career.

users.name: Alexa Potter
users.about: I've never actually tried coffee before, but this is the coolest app I've ever seen, so I couldn't miss out. I plan on having my first cup of coffee using this app. Thank you so much for the opportunity to start this new hobby of coffee drinking. I think I'll start with a double shot in the dark with extra sugar, I've heard that's a great starter drink.

users.name: Blake Smith
users.about: I am a graduate student at Belmont University, but am originally from Pennsylvania. I am looking to make some new social connections in the Nashville area. I love doing homework and hanging out at coffee shops, so I would love to meet some people with similar interests as me. I look forward to discovering this new city and new friends!

users.name: Ishaan Ahad
users.about: My name is Ishaan, I am from New York City, but recently moved to Nashville. I am Founder and CEO of a tech startup, so I love getting out to coffee shops in the area to work on my laptop. Coming from NYC coffee shops, I am always looking for the best espresso pulls, no frills coffee only.

users.name: Lizzy Ng
users.about: Hi! I am Lizzzy, and I just want to explore and have fun being social in different coffee shops! I love to travel and explore with my friends.

users.name: Herbert Foster
users.about: I am interested in finding the best quality coffee experience. I only care about coffee taste in a quiet and cozy atmosphere. Look forward to learning more with this app.

users.name: Irina Kovalinko
users.about: I am Irina, I moved to the US three years ago, and love the coffee culture of my new city. I love espresso drinks, usually cortado! Please recommend any places with bold roasts.

users.name: Edwin Jones
users.about: I want to explore coffee shops of all variety. I love discovering new coffee beans, blends, or brewing methods. I frequently bring my kiddos along with me, so somewhere that has some non-caffeinated drinks is a plus.

posts.text: this place is great, we all love it, we come here every time my grandma has a birthday!

This isn't really a coffee shop, so if you see it pop up on your results, save your time and go elsewhere. This is primarily a cocktail bar/lounge. They DO serve coffee, but it's not great.
This place has great baked goods! Wouldn't necessarily come for the coffee experiences but the food is yummy.
Coffee is subpar and the atmosphere was very crowded. Decent place to go with friends, or stop in quickly. Would not recommend for work or calm atmosphere.
More of a restaurant, not really a coffee shop. Go for the food and have some okay coffee if you are wanting an overpriced breakfast.
This place is full of tourists and the menu is too large. Try doing black coffee and espresso based classics well first before branching out. Pass!
This place was the first visit I made in Nashville. Decent coffee and nice location. I would prefer something a little more intimate next time, but a great option if you are in the area.
This place is fun and cute, but I had a bad experience trying to order a traditional cappuccino. There is only ONE size of cappuccino, please don't ask if I would like a 12oz, 16oz, or 20oz!
I like this place, but it is very busy. Food is nice and coffee menu has lots of selection. Be ready to wait in line if you go during weekend.
Not a coffee shop obviously, but I had to say something.

I love 12South neighborhood, but it was better 5 years ago before it was quite so developed and busy. I wish this place was still on my regular rotation, but I just cant stand the crowds anymore. Such is Nashville, I guess.

Very cool place! Definitely worth a trip if you are nearby or looking for a new adventure. I love the food options and the coffee is surprisingly good. They use locally roasted beans and keep it simple.
Go for the brunch, not as a coffee shop necessarily. I do enjoy this place though! Great place to go with those friends who are in town for a visit.
I did not enjoy this place! Do NOT recommend! SO rude!
I added to my favorites because it is the most affordable great breakfast food with great flavor and spices! Great locally roasted beans and coffee.
Best sweet treats around! Highly recommend if you want some donuts and coffee. Great seasonal rotation of donuts and flavored drinks.

This place was good, but not great. I liked the coffee, but most of their drinks seem to contain lots of sweeteners and flavor additives. If you want that type of drink this is your place. If you want something more traditional, you might look elsewhere.
Tried this location while visiting Chattanooga, and it was great! Pretty busy, but with great location that's to be expected.
One of the best spots in Knoxville, located in the heart of "The Old City." Highly recommend the flavored drinks if you're into that.
Nice new location near Historic West Side of downtown Cookeville. Outdoor seating under a covered front porch is really nice. Good coffee, usually busy on the weekends though. Closed on Sunday :(

Right on the downtown strip of cute shops and restaurants in Historic West Side of Cookeville. Not tons of seating, but the decor is always awesome and fits the season. Good coffee and really nice people. Best coffee shop in Cookeville!
Neat place, I added to my favorites just in case I am out in the area again looking for coffee. Not necessarily my Go-to in town though.
Very close to University of Memphis, so usually busy with students. But a great in and out place to get good food and coffee if you're in the area.
Favorite coffee in Memphis!
Great spot in Knoxville, right in the heart of downtown.
Donuts. Yes.
Close to the river in Chatt. Great spot, nice people, good baked goods.
A must visit if you are in Chattanooga. North of the river in a great location.
Great place to visit in Knoxville!
Cool cozy international breakfast options!
Great baked goods, obviously, based on the title. But also good coffee and convenient location!

This place is loved by locals, and was one of the original local coffee shops to establish itself in Cookeville. Cozy atmosphere, but sometimes slow service when they get busy with all the college students.
Great for those who have dietary restrictions! Very good vegan and vegetarian options. The coffee was okay, but not great.
Amazing location and coffee! Love the home made poptarts.
Some of the best donuts you can get in TN! Love the maple glazed. The coffee is also pretty solid if you stick to the classics.
Not so much a coffee place, but they do have good coffee if you stick with the classics. GREAT breakfast though.
Best coffee in Cookeville! New location looks amazing, they roast the beans in-house and sell bags for a very good price.

coffeePreferences.name: Traditional
coffeePreferences.description: I enjoy traditional coffees, typically with no sugar or flavor additives. Drinks such as black coffee, cappuccino, cortado, flat white, etc.

coffeePreferences.name: Sweet
coffeePreferences.description: I enjoy flavored coffees or seasonal flavored brews. Drinks such as caramel macchiato, pumpkin spice latte, hazelnut coffee, smores latte, frappuccino, etc.

coffeePreferences.name: Exploratory
coffeePreferences.description: I enjoy trying coffee which is brewed in various ways. I want to explore trraditional and non-traditional extraction methods such as pour over, siphon pot, french press, Aeropress, Moka pot, etc.

coffeePreferences.name: International
coffeePreferences.description: I enjoy, or want to try, coffees from diverse regions of the world. Drinks I might enjoy are Turkish Coffee, Cafe Cubano, Vietnamese Coffee, etc.

coffeePreferences.name: Cold
coffeePreferences.description: I enjoy cold coffee-based drinks year-round, and prefere for my frequent shops to have plenty of iced options. Drinks I enjoy are cold brew, iced latte, iced americano, etc.

coffeePreferences.name: Dietary-Restrictions
coffeePreferences.description: I have a need for coffee shops with plenty of health-conscious options, either out of necessity or preference. Health-conscious options are look for are dairy-free, gluten free, caffeine free, etc.

coffeePreferences.name: Powerful
coffeePreferences.description: I always look for coffee that packs a punch! I have no interest in creams, sugars, or any flavor other than dark, strong, coffee. Drink I usually go for are a shot in the dark, dark roast, americano, sidecar, etc.

atmospherePreferences.name: Lively
atmospherePreferences.description: I prefer lively coffee shops where hanging out with friends and being social is encouraged. I don't mind waiting in line or socializing with new people.

atmospherePreferences.name: Cozy
atmospherePreferences.description: I prefer cozy coffee shops which are warm and inviting, with comfortable seating, soft lighting, and a sense of intimacy.

atmospherePreferences.name: Hipster
atmospherePreferences.description: I preferr hipster coffee shops which are trendy and fashionable with unique decor, artisnal coffee, added bonus if there are plenty of places for insta stories.

atmospherePreferences.name: Quaint
atmospherePreferences.description: I prefer quaint coffee shops whichh are small and charming, maybe with a touch of old-world charm.

atmospherePreferences.name: Low-Key
atmospherePreferences.description: I prefer a low-key coffee shop where I can get work done around others without being interrupted by large crowds or too much noise. Or just enjoy some perosnal time.

atmospherePreferences.name: Multi-Cultural
atmospherePreferences.description: I prefer cultural coffee shops which represent a diverse community or culture. I love to explore foods, drinks, and vibes from different people from around the world.

atmospherePreferences.name: Corporate
atmospherePreferences.description: I prefer the tried and true coffee shops owned by national corporations. I love the convenience, especially when there is a drive thru.
